cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) tools such as taggers and parsers. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves the automation of neuropsychological tests. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper evaluates different embedding induction methods for the sentence boundary detection task. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as some of the embedding induction methods may involve neural networks. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with speech transcripts.
